HEADWORD: cat-a-mountain
<hw>cat"-a-moun`tain</hw></mhw>
<pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>the bushy-tailed European wildcat
(<spn>Felis silvestris</spn>) resembling the domestic tabby and regarded
as the ancestor of the domestic cat.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> European wildcat, <spn>Felis
silvestris</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
